---

This notice covers `packages/plugin-traveller`, the optional Fair Use Policy compatibility layer
described in the Spec (§1, §15) that lets `packages/engine` (which contains zero setting content
and zero Traveller terms — INV-1) consume Traveller-specific data via a one-time, user-driven
import of a travellermap.com SEC export. Nothing under `packages/engine` or `content/` reproduces
Traveller rulebook text; per the Spec's fair-use hygiene requirement, all game content in this
repository is original dice math and original entries, never rulebook table prose.

Per the Fair Use Policy's FAQ item 1(c) (Traveller Fair Use Policy, PDF, FAQ revision Sept 3,
2024, https://www.mongoosepublishing.com/pages/traveller-licensing), Mongoose Publishing must
also be notified directly by email (sales@mongoosepublishing.com) that this site exists at
https://gruevyhat.github.io/telemetry-engine/. That notification is logged in
`docs/tasks/M0-00.md` once sent — this file alone is the required on-site disclaimer, not proof
the notification itself has gone out.
